<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="absolutely-adv">absolutely <strong><em>adv</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'æbsəlu:tli/    美 /'æbsəlu:tli/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-quite">1.★ <strong>完全地；绝对地 (quite)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He made his reasons for resigning absolutely clear.
他把辞职的理由讲得一清二楚。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— People don’t care enough about the environment.
人们对环境关心不够。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— I think you’re absolutely right. 
我认为你说的完全正确。</p><footer>外研③ – 4</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>[用于强调] 确实：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>When I’m reading a book, <strong>absolutely nothing</strong> can get my attention. 
当我读书时，其他任何东西都不能引起我的注意。</p><footer>北师大⑥ – 17</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— You’re sure there’s <strong>absolutely no</strong> hot water?
你确定确实没有热水吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— No, none.
是的，没有。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="absolutely">Absolutely!</h3>
<p>1.<strong>正是；当然：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— They could have told us, couldn't they?
他们本来可以告诉我们的，不是吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Absolutely! 
正是！</p></div>

<h3 id="absolutely-not">Absolutely not!</h3>
<p>1.<strong>绝对不行；当然不：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Do you let your kids travel alone at night? 
你让自己的孩子们晚上单独外出吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Absolutely not! 
当然不!</p></div></div>